Signs of the end.
What indicates that Russia is emerging from the crisis?
Economists have seen signs of Russia’s exit from the longest recession in 20 years.
According to analysts polled by the Bloomberg agency, the GDP of the Russian Federation shows positive dynamics - in the second quarter of GDP decreased by 0.8% in annual terms.
This figure is the lowest since the beginning of 2015.
According to the latest data of Rosstat, the decline of the Russian economy in the second quarter slowed to 0.6%.
The Central Bank and the Ministry of Economic Development have also recently declared stabilization of the situation.
In front is a slow rise.
According to experts of the Central Bank, the recession in the Russian economy remained in the past.
“The index estimate of Russian GDP indicates that the recession has been left behind, and the slow growth of the economy is ahead,” the Bank of Russia said in the bulletin “What the trends are talking about.”
The modular estimate of GDP for the current quarter of the regulator has increased to 0.4%, the estimate for the fourth quarter is 0.5%.
According to the representative of the Ministry of Economic Development, during the second quarter, the decline of the GDP of the Russian Federation stopped in the second quarter, amounting to 0.2%.
In the second quarter, the seasonally adjusted GDP decline was 0.2% compared to the previous quarter.
But during the quarter, the decline stopped: in April it amounted to 0.2%, and in May and June the change in GDP was within 0-0.15", - quoted the representative of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs RIA "Novosti".
The slowdown in the Russian economy over the past five quarters indicates that “the bottom has passed.”
Among other markers pointing to signs of a revival of the national economy, Bloomberg calls the growth in demand for electricity and rail transport, the revival of business.
If you make an amendment to the fact that the year is leap year, it is clear that the dynamics in the plus 1% of electricity consumption can be half due to an additional working day.
Add to this a lower average annual temperature in the first quarter.
The next argument is the growth of freight transport, but it is difficult to get accurate data here, and plus or minus 0.5% of the half-yearly volume can also be explained by seasonality,” explains Kirill Yakovenko from ALOR BROKER.
However, there are other, more obvious signs of stabilization of the Russian economy.
For example, a reduction in price pressure.
In July, the consumer price index stood at 7.2% compared to 15.6% in the same month last year.
Moreover, Rosstat has been recording deflation for the past two weeks.
Prices in Russia fell for the first time in five years.
If you look at the dynamics of the exchange rate of the ruble, which, although showed strong fluctuations at the beginning of the year, at the end of August since the beginning of the year has strengthened by 12%.
This is also one of the signs of recovery, which should be followed by indicators from the real sector of the economy," Yakovenko emphasizes.
In addition, there has been an increase in industrial production in Russia since April.
In June, the figure increased by 1.7%.
The rate of decline in foreign trade turnover is slowing from -32.8% in January 2016 to -20.7% in May.
Positive dynamics are also demonstrated by the situation in the labor market, where the unemployment rate has decreased to 5.4%.
It was down only in September 2015 (5.2%).
Despite the well-being of the labor market, the question of real disposable incomes of the population leaves much to be desired.
In annual terms, the figure decreases by 4.8 per cent.
This factor can slow down the recovery of the economy, as household spending makes a significant contribution to GDP.
As a rule, their share in the structure of the economy exceeds 50%.
In addition to low consumer activity, as a risk factor for economic growth can also be called a tough policy of the Bank of Russia.
The regulator keeps the rate at 10.5%, which does not have the best effect on the real sector.
A negative factor is the insufficiently high level of investment, which inhibits the development of industrial potential.
But in general, it can be assumed that by the end of the year the rate of decline of the Russian economy will slow down to -0.5% against -3.7% in 2015", - says analyst of Forex Club Group Irina Rogova.
