The Tax Code provides for the exemption from NFPA of compensation payments established by law within the approved norms related to compensation for damage caused by injury or other damage to health.
The delivery of milk to workers engaged in work with harmful working conditions according to the established norms is provided for in Article 222 of the Criminal Code of the Russian Federation.
At the same time, the norms and conditions of issuance are established by the order of the Ministry of Health and Social Development of Russia of February 16, 2009 No. 45n.
According to this document, the free delivery of milk or other equivalent food products is made to workers in the days of actual employment in work with harmful working conditions, due to the presence of harmful production factors in the workplace.
On the basis of these norms, the FNS of Russia in the letter under consideration came to the conclusion that on the basis of paragraph 2 paragraph 3 of Article 217 of the Constitution of the Russian Federation, the income in the form of the value of milk issued to employees in the days of actual employment at work with harmful working conditions in accordance with the provisions of Article 217 of the Constitution of the Russian Federation is exempt from taxation.
The Moscow “Gazstroybank” was left without a license of the Central Bank.
On Friday, August 12, 2016, the Central Bank of Russia revoked the license to carry out banking operations at the Joint-Stock Commercial Bank "GAZSTROYBANK", registered in Moscow.
According to the regulator, JSC JSC Gasstroybank conducted a high-risk credit policy related to the placement of funds in low-quality assets.
An adequate assessment of the risks taken at the request of the supervisory authority and a reliable reflection of the value of the bank’s assets led to the creation of grounds for the credit organization to implement measures to prevent bankruptcy.
In addition, the credit institution was involved in the conduct of dubious transit operations.
The bank has appointed a temporary administration for the period of validity until the moment of appointment to the competitive manager or liquidator.
The powers of the executive bodies of the credit organization in accordance with federal laws are suspended.
JSC ACB "GAZTROYBANK" - participant of the deposit insurance system.
We remind that the payment of insurance compensation to depositors of the bank, including individual entrepreneurs, in accordance with Federal Law No. 177-FZ "On insurance of deposits of individuals in banks of the Russian Federation" is provided in the amount of 100% of the balance of funds, but not more than 1.4 million rubles in total per one depositor.
Payments, according to the Deposit Insurance Agency, will begin no later than August 26, 2016.
According to the report, on August 1, 2016, the assets of JSC JSC GASTROYBANK took 335 place in the banking system of the Russian Federation.
