At this stage of news reporting, I would probably look seriously puzzled, scrolling racks with Bosanov’s collections.
The “trophy” aspect of the revival is what Johnny, 42, noticed working in Sounds of the Universe (data count: three middle-aged men).
“Someone came in recently and said, ‘I don’t have a record player, but I want to buy a Radiohead record so we can put a regiment on it,’” he says.
It's not a big percentage, but it definitely happens.
The more the product, the less the music.
