The government has extended the period for the destruction of sanctions products
The government has extended until the end of 2017 the period of destruction of food products prohibited for import into Russia.
The relevant decree was signed by Prime Minister Dmitry Medvedev, it is published on the official portal of legal information.
The embargo on countries that imposed anti-Russian sanctions because of the situation in Ukraine was introduced in our country in August 2014.
Subsequently, the ban was extended several times, now it is valid until December 31, 2017.
In Russia, it is forbidden to import certain types of agricultural products, raw materials and food from the United States, European Union countries, Canada, Australia, Norway, Ukraine, Albania, Montenegro, Iceland and Liechtenstein.
In particular, meat and meat products, fish, seafood, vegetables, fruits and dairy products were banned.
The disposal of food imported into the country to circumvent the embargo has been carried out in Russia since August 2015.
In the first quarter of 2016 alone, about 100 tonnes of prohibited products were withdrawn from sales.
