The largest M&A deal was launched in the pension market - "KIT Finance Pension Administrator" launched the process of combining four controlled NPFs.
As a result, based on the "Gazfond Pension savings" will be created NPF with the amount of savings of about 373 billion rubles.
About the launch of the procedure of combining four pension funds - "KIT Finance", "Promagrofond", "Heritage" and "Gazfond Pension savings" - yesterday the owner of 100% of funds of LLC "KIT Finance Pension Administrator".
"Reorganization is carried out in agreement with the Central Bank, subject to the requirement of non-deterioration of the terms of the existing contracts," the company said in a statement.
The merger is carried out on the basis of "Gazfond Pension savings".
According to Oleg Byaloshitsky, the general director of this NPF, the association of funds allows to solve several tasks: expanding the geography of the presence, concentrating resources for development, reducing costs, replicating the best practices of each of the funds and optimizing corporate governance.
According to him, the target period for completion of consolidation is the second quarter of 2017.
As a result of the merger of the NPF "Gazfond Pension savings" will become the largest player in the OPP market.
According to data as of March 31, the amount of pension savings of the merging funds exceeded 373 billion rubles.
As it follows from the reports on the website of the funds, the beneficiaries of their owner - "KIT Finance Pension Administrator" - are currently Anatoly Gavrilenko (through controlled LLC owns 65%) and NPF "Gazfond" (35%).
However, the group itself launched much later competitors.
Thus, the group controlled by the O1 NPF "Future" absorbed "Stalfond" at the beginning of this year.
Currently, this combined NPF joins the Uralsib and Russian Standard funds.
“Unification into a single structure, in addition to reducing costs, is necessary to solve structural problems,” says Nikolay Sidorov, the general director of NPF “Future”.
Active work on the consolidation of funds since April is going on in the pension group "Safmar" - NPF "European", "Education and Science" and "Regionfond" should be merged into NPF "Safmar" by the end of this year.
In 2017, NPF "Trust" will join them.
“The pooling of funds will have the effect of increasing control over risks, operational processes and costs,” Safmar said.
The pause in the pooling of funds endured by the “KIT Finance Pension Administrator” may be caused by several reasons, experts say.
Until recently, NPFs could not buy back more than 40% of the volume of infrastructure bonds issued by the group.
After the amendments to the resolution of the Central Bank in March of this year on a number of issuers that meet the requirements of the regulator, such restrictions no longer exist.
If necessary, the entire issue can be bought out by one major player,” says Yuri Nogin, director of the rating group of the financial institutions of AKRA.
Several NPF executives from the top 15 on assets, another possible cause of the pause, called the division of spheres of influence and, as a result, personnel appointments in a single fund, which should have been agreed by the owners of the group.
Yesterday Anatoly Gavrilenko was unavailable for comment.
