According to the results of the inspection, the Federal Antimonopoly Service decided to punish Google, said Deputy Head of FAS Alexei Dotsenko.
The fine must be paid within 60 days after the entry into force of the decree.
The FAS concluded that the law on protection of competition should be observed by all companies, including transnational corporations.
In turn, Google intends to first study the solution and only then determine with further actions: execute it or challenge it.
The Federal Antimonopoly Service recognized the company as a violation of the competition law in September last year and ordered to adjust the contracts until December 18.
Google did not agree to this.
Since then, the company and the department have been conducting legal proceedings.
The FAS noted that, despite the fine, they are discussing with Google the possibility of concluding a world agreement.
