Haunted between Angola and South Africa, Namibia suffered greatly during a long struggle against apartheid.
However, after independence from South Africa in 1990, this country with a population of 2.4 million people has achieved tremendous success, especially in the last few years.
The main reason for Namibia’s success is that the government pays great attention to education.
While people in developed countries perceive free primary and secondary education as a matter of course, in many poor countries, secondary and even primary schools require tuition.
Moreover, governments are often advised to introduce tuition fees to “reimbursement costs”.
In Namibia, however, primary school education is free of charge.
